<title>USA: Havas eyes Bouygues's Ciby unit - report.</title>
<headline>Havas eyes Bouygues's Ciby unit - report.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>French communications company Havas is considering buying film production company Ciby 2000, a unit of Bouygues, Daily Variety said on Thursday, but Walt Disney was not a potential buyer.</p>
<p>French media reports have said Bouygues is trying to sell Ciby, which produced movies like The Piano, Underground and Secrets &amp; Lies.</p>
<p>News Corp was seen as another possible bidder, the report said.</p>
<p>--New York newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
</text>
